Package com.whirvis.jraknet.peer

Componenents used to interface with RakNet peers, connections to either a server or a client machine.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    RakNetClientPeerMessenger
    Represents an object that has the ability to send messages to a RakNetClientPeer.
    RakNetPeerMessenger
    Represents an object that has the ability to send messages to a RakNetPeer.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    RakNetClientPeer
    A client connection that handles login and other client related protocols.
    RakNetPeer
    Represents a connection to another machine, be it a server or a client.
    RakNetPeer.ConcurrentMessageIndexList
    Used to store the message index for received reliable packets in a condensed fashion.
    RakNetServerPeer
    A server connection that handles login and other server related protocols.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    RakNetState
    Represents the current status of a connection in a RakNetPeer.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    PacketOverloadException
    Signals that a RakNetPeer has attempted to send too many packets at once.
    SplitQueueOverflowException
    Signals that there are too many split packets in the queue at once.
    TimeoutException
    Signals that a RakNetPeer has timed out.
